            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$3,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$1,500</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$150K</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">$149 (one-time)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-emerald-600 font-semibold">No target</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$4,500</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$2,000</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Winning Days -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 mb-5">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-amber-900 mb-1">Winning Days Objective</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-amber-800">
        With the Express Funded Account you need to make a profit of <strong>$200 or more on 5 separate trading days</strong>, which will demonstrate to Topstep that you can be consistently profitable as a funded trader.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Scaling Plan -->
    <h4 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Topstep Scaling Plan</h4>
    <p class="mb-3">
      Another objective you need to follow is Topstep's scaling plan, which is essentially a risk management plan. If trading with a $50K account you can't exceed <strong>5 lots</strong> of exposure. If you're trading with a $100K account the max is <strong>10 lots</strong>, and with a $150K it's <strong>15 lots</strong>.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-3">
      As your account increases or decreases in value, so will the number of lots you can open. Your new balance is only calculated at the beginning of the next trading day at 5:00pm CST.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-5">
      If you make an error by opening too many lots, it can result in your account being suspended, although if you correct the mistake within <strong>10 seconds</strong>, Topstep won't take any action.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2 mb-5">
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-center">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">$50K Account</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">5 lots max</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-center">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">$100K Account</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">10 lots max</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-center">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">$150K Account</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">15 lots max</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- 3. LIVE FUNDED ACCOUNT                                          -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="mb-10">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 text-white text-xs font-black flex items-center justify-center">3</span>
      Live Funded Account
    </h3>

    <p class="mb-3">
      In the Live Funded Account, traders use real capital to trade in live markets. There are no subscription or activation fees, but the stakes are higher.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The primary rule here is to avoid breaching the <strong>Maximum Loss Limit</strong>, as this will result in the permanent closure of the account.
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-5">
      <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
        <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Account Size</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Fees</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Profit Target</th>
